President Obama and Prime Minister Harper of Canada announced a joint effort to address the global economic recession and strengthen the international financial system. They discussed economic recovery measures, including lowering taxes, ensuring access to credit, and stimulating economic growth through spending. The leaders also established a Clean Energy Dialogue to promote clean energy technologies and combat climate change. They agreed to expand clean energy research and development, develop and deploy clean energy technology, and build a more efficient electric grid based on clean and renewable generation. Additionally, they pledged to work together on international security challenges, such as Afghanistan, and promote effective discussions at the upcoming NATO Summit and Summit of the Americas.